snippet: Mustafa Suleiman, the Egyptian prosecutor in the trial of former President Hosni Mubarak, said the government’s internal security forces “deliberately sought to mislead justice.”
abstract: Mustafa Suleiman, Egyptian prosecutor in trial of former Pres Hosni Mubarak, says the government’s internal security forces had obstructed his case, suggesting that the nation's law enforcement officials are not all committed to a vigorous prosecution of their former boss.
lead_paragraph: Mustafa Suleiman, the Egyptian prosecutor in the trial of former President Hosni Mubarak, said the government’s internal security forces “deliberately sought to mislead justice.”
